The Saudi Arabian national census has started publishing migration data by administrative area (place of birth and place of current residence) since 2004, specifically for the native population. Analyses were carried out to calculate the following:In-migration rate = (Number of persons entering an administrative area/population in the area)∗1000. That is, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
